description:
In its Infectious Disease Regulation from 31.7.2020 Kiribati announced the establishment of a new task force to e.g. to develop a Preparedness and Response Plan; Develop preventive measures and coordinate efforts at all levels to prevent an infectious disease (e.g. COVID-19) from reaching Kiribati;
Coordinate responses to any suspected cases, local transmission and outbreak in the country;advise all relevant Ministries, Departments and Agencies of any latest infectious disease (e.g. COVID-19) information, risk assessments and all implementation measures prescribed under these Regulations and related protocol. Provide information and awareness to the general public through radio,
television, printed materials and other media platforms; Provide a situation analysis of the current capacity of Kiribati to address an infectious disease (e.g. COVID-19); Deliberate on the conditions necessary for the prevention of the infectious disease and protecting and enhancing the public health; Provide a list of all countries that has been declared and confirmed to have infectious disease; Receive reports under regulation 5(3) from sub-committees and delegate actions, Coordinate meetings.

The taskforce is comprised of:
-Director of Public Health;
-Commissioner of Police;
-International Health Regulation National Focal Point/Personal
-Senior State Attorney
-Officers in charge of all relevant border control agencies;
-Community leaders;
-Non-governmental agencies;
-any other persons selected
